tip.text: Dim Sum was done well, but not in a traditional style. Great for groups. V spacious n cosy. Didn't like the custard pao. Porridge was nice.
Delicious and value for money Dim Sum. Friendly service. They have an English menu. Coffee is an extra 20HKD from the shop next door but they'll collect it for you. Lovely cafe.
It's an awesome place to watch fishes we will not get to see unless we are professional divers. Best learning place for kids.

location.address: Aqua City, The Waterfront, Ocean Park
formattedAddress: Aqua City, The Waterfront, Ocean Park

tip.text: People are obviously here for the biscuits. We were told they change the design of the tins too. It's becoming a collectible series. Needless to say, these are the v buttery n dense cookies. Delicious
Char Siu rice is not bad.
Pork Ribs not bad. Lotus leaf rice is ok too. Good for a quick breakfast.
The beef noodles are to die for. Meat is supersoft, noodles chewy, broth filling. The queue snakes round the block, even in the rain. Come at non mealtime hours to skip the Qs. Starts at 12.30pm.
The old ladies serving are friendly. English menu available. Good coffee. Pork ribs are really nice. Nice place for breakfast. Near Jordan MTR.
They serve 3 main dishes - wanton mee, fish meat noodles, beef noodles. Good value for money. Exit at Tsim Sha Tsui MTR. The wanton is generous and meaty. 30HKD per bowl.

location.address: Shop 3, G/F, Lee West Commercial Bldg, 1-3 Hart Ave
formattedAddress: Shop 3, G/F, Lee West Commercial Bldg, 1-3 Hart Ave

venue.name: Lung Kee Wonton (龍記招牌雲吞)

tip.text: Awesome place to visit especially for families. Will go again. V convenient to buy tickets at tourist info centre at MTR, then take bus 629 at terminus. Signs along the way. Have Pandas!

venue.name: Ocean Park Hong Kong 香港海洋公園 (香港海洋公園)

tip.text: Food is delicious. Prices are steep. I like that they serve little buns to soak up the pork rib sauce. Service friendly.

venue.name: Luk Yu Tea House (陸羽茶室)

tip.text: Egg custard with almond is delicious. Smooth. Service a little impatient and they may have overcharged me. Saw a long queue in the afternoon (sunday) but there was no queue in the evening.

venue.name: Australia Dairy Company (澳洲牛奶公司)

tip.text: The noodles are cooked al dante and so fine. Every wonton has 2 plump shrimps. Patient service with English menu. Portions a bit small but satisfying. Delicious!

venue.name: Mak's Noodle (麥奀記雲吞麵世家)

tip.text: Roast Goose to die for!!! They don't serve roast duck though. Service is good. Must try.
Bestest fish head curry banana leaf rice. Closed on Tuesday
Seafood is not the only thing they serve here. The non seafood dishes are awesome, especially the ribeye and lamb rack. They serve oysters too.

formattedAddress: Level 6 (Canteen), Lam Soon Industrial Building (63 Hillview Avenue)

tip.text: Mutton soup runs out quickly. Great for a rainy day.
Pizzas. Could have refilled our water but didn't.

formattedAddress: #01-17A Raffles City Shopping Centre (252 North Bridge Road (opp Raffles Hotel))

tip.text: Love the prawn beehoon mee. Ample parking at the back along Kandahar and Baghdad streets. The ngoh hiang stall next to it serves good complement to the noodles. Takeaway available.
Buy sushi from the supermarket and eat at the  tables near the escalator. Save on service charge.
Reasonably priced. Nice relaxing coffeeshop ambience. If driving, go to the industrial park n park at the multi-storey car park. Food was alright.
Peaceful respite from the busy city. Near Xi Men Ting shopping district. Buy breakfast takeaway from nearby shops n go there for a quiet picnic.  Public toilets available

venue.name: 228 Peace Memorial Park (二二八和平紀念公園)

tip.text: Must try restaurant! Good service and great food. They have individual set menus ranging from 500NT to 1600NT, almost 9 courses
Great place for a snack n grab free maps from the tourist bureau post.

venue.name: 關西服務區 Guanxi Service Area

tip.text: Good stopover place for dinner but food court can get crowded during meal times.
Fish restaurant. Good value for money and ample parking. Try the mango ice cream shaped like a mango for the fun of it :-)
200NT for a plate of fresh sashimi is insanely affordable. There are set meals you can order from the side stalls inside the market n they are awesome.
Cheap place to get a Latte 65NT or a sundae 40NT after the food crawl. Quiet n suitable drop off point/meeting point.
Street food is cheap n awesome. About 100NT for most single person portions. They don't really have bins but the vendors will get rid of your trash if u buy something from them. Try the wild boar.
The Char Kway Tiow auntie was distracted with chatting and fried me an extra big portion. 😊
Great place to chill by the river. Parking is usually ample but it's within the ERP zone on the weekdays.
There are tables next to the beach. Nice n breezy. Awesome place to chill. Reasonable prices.
Yummy rojak!!
Mixed intestines Mee Sua. Yummy!!!
I love their service. We didn't speak French but they were polite and patient. Have had a few meals here.

formattedAddress: 6 rue de la Glacière (rue de la Glacière)

tip.text: Awesome durians. I ate one that was creamy, sweet, bitter, and left a slight tingling sensation on the tongue which some folks think it's because it was freshly picked. Free water available.
Roast duck here is not bad. Char Kway Teow ok too but no cockles. Service can be better. Visit outside lunch hours if poss cos it's completely packed. Conveniently located next to MRT exit.

formattedAddress: Level B4, ION Orchard (2 Orchard Turn)

tip.text: I love this snack! Chewy dough balls with sweet and crunchy peanut filling. Never fail to eat it when I'm here!

formattedAddress: #01-10 Golden Mile Food Centre (505 Beach Road)

tip.text: Chilli crab, marmite chicken, crab bee hoon etc. Good value for money but parking is a war zone. Best to park at the workshop area then take a 3min walk over.
Interesting collection of old toys and memorabilia. Cafe below and roof top bar that opens at 3pm. Nostalgic.
Explanation of the Battle of Waterloo and the history of the French Republic. Lots of uniforms on display. Augmented reality displays. Great for kids and history students.
Very modern with many many exhibits. Tells a very clear and riveting story of the citizens and soldiers in Bastogne during WW2
Inspiring story of Herge. Learnt about the process of making comics. Of course lots of information about Tintin. Parking on site not possible. No photos of exhibits only of foyer.
Newly renovated museum underground. Awesome exhibits v modern
How comic strip are made and the different artists. Awesome  gift shop below.
Learnt about the life of Jules Verne. He created about 30 stories in this house. Fascinating insights into his life, and his passion for travel and writing.
D-Day Museum. Free parking. Bring the kids n teach them something about sacrifice n duty.

venue.name: Normandy American Cemetery and Memorial (Cimetière américain de Colleville-sur-Mer)

tip.text: Historic town. John Steele was the paratrooper whose chute was stuck on the church spire. Airborne museum in the vicinity but close at year end.
V friendly service. Appreciate them introducing the produce to us even though we spoke no French.
Fresh seafood. Any fresher you have to go into the water to get it yourself.
Decent ingredients in Mee Pok. Cosy w lots of seating. Good for Saturday morning breakie if you want to avoid the breakfast hordes in ikea.
Waffles are ok. Fried chicken is v nice. Good for a quick night snack.
Place to go for bitter gourd fix. Beef hor fun is v good n generous; good wok hei.
Nice porridge
